column2: A form of government in which the head is not granted right to rule due to divine right, but merely because they own the most land and merchants.
A form of feudalism in which the head of state is either a god, high priest, or seen as the physical form of a god.
A form of government with the head of state usually have complete power or almost complete power through their own strength or that of like minded allies.
A form of government with the head of state being the commander of the most powerful army.
A form of government in which only mages or those with magical ancestors are permited to rule and own land.
